There is an invisible platform that you have to jump to first in  order 
to reach the doorway.  Keep close to the wall on the right,  do a small 
running  jump onto the invisible platform,  you should hear some music, 
turn left a bit and do a running jump diagonally across to the doorway. 
Once inside kill the technician and get the yellow key that's hidden at 
the back of the room.

Exit the room and drop off of the ledge,  pick up the medikits and make 
your  way to the doorway next to the raised platform.  You are now in a 
 corridor that has vented walls.  Continue along this corridor, kill the 
tramp, pick up the medikit and shield.

Now  enter a large room that contains a tall column.  Kill a tramp  and 
technician,  pick up the ammo and medikit, use the lift platform in the 
tall column and go up,  kill another tramp.  Turn right and do a couple 
of jumps to get across to another ledge.

There are stairs to the right,  go up them and turn left, go left again 
at  the  doorway and carry along.  Kill the technician and pick up  the 
shields, save the game at the exit terminal.

Right,  that's your lot. I've already done way too much for you. You've 
now got all the keys, completed he primary mission, and found where the 
exit is.  The secondary mission is nearby and so is the burger bar,  if 
you don't mind walking. You passed the doorway that led to them.

Here  are a couple of hints that might help you,  the switch that opens 
the  secondary  mission door is hidden in a train.  You'll also find  a 
transporter  pad  behind it,  you'll have to use it to get back to  the 
exit. When you use the transporter pad you'll find yourself in the back 
of  a lorry on the loading bay.  That's where you picked up the red key 
earlier.

There's quite a lot of this level that hasn't even visited,  as well as 
a few hidden rooms and objects that have still to be picked up.

 HAVE FUN!

